# ✅ 1. Losing `this` in Event Handlers

### ❌ Bug:

```javascript
const user = {
  name: "Ravi",
  printName() {
    console.log(this.name);
  }
};

document.getElementById("btn").addEventListener("click", user.printName);
```

### 😱 Output:

    undefined

👉 Why?

*   `this` becomes **button element**, not `user`

***

### ✅ Fix:

```javascript
document.getElementById("btn")
  .addEventListener("click", user.printName.bind(user));
```

OR

```javascript
addEventListener("click", () => user.printName());
```

***

# ✅ 2. `this` Lost in setTimeout

***

### ❌ Bug:

```javascript
const user = {
  name: "Anu",
  greet() {
    setTimeout(function () {
      console.log(this.name);
    }, 1000);
  }
};

user.greet();
```

### 😱 Output:

    undefined

👉 Because:

    this → window (or undefined in strict mode)

***

### ✅ Fix:

```javascript
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log(this.name);
}, 1000);
```

✔ Arrow function keeps lexical `this`

***

# ✅ 3. Method passed as Callback

***

### ❌ Bug:

```javascript
const obj = {
  value: 10,
  getValue() {
    return this.value;
  }
};

function execute(fn) {
  console.log(fn());
}

execute(obj.getValue);
```

### 😱 Output:

    undefined

👉 `this` lost when function is passed

***

### ✅ Fix:

```javascript
execute(obj.getValue.bind(obj));
```

***

# ✅ 4. React Class Component Bug

***

### ❌ Bug:

```javascript
class MyComponent extends React.Component {
  constructor() {
    super();
    this.state = { count: 0 };
  }

  handleClick() {
    console.log(this.state.count);
